data.title: Oriental Museum, Durham University · Ancient Egyptian Animal Bio Bank
data.meta_description: an online database of animal mummies based on research at The University of Manchester, UK
data.text:
Items in the collection

AEABB176

EXTERNAL APPEARANCE

Cyclindrical bundle with false head, eyes, ears and nose. Horizontal striped bandaging. Previously conserved - netting around the body.

AEABB175

EXTERNAL APPEARANCE

Conical shaped with false head and feet with horizontal striped linen wrapping. Some of the breast area decoration is lost.

AEABB174

EXTERNAL APPEARANCE

Dark and light brown linen wrappings. False head, face and ears. Hole in front area with reeds visible protruding slightly and laid longitudinally.

AEABB173

EXTERNAL APPEARANCE

Partially unwrapped falcon with beak and feet exposed. Linen appears to be one piece shrouded around the bird.

AEABB172

EXTERNAL APPEARANCE

Fragmented pieces of animal mummy kept in a perspex box. Included linen, resin and bone. Long bone identified as feline

AEABB171

EXTERNAL APPEARANCE

Dark brown wrappings with face painted on. On a display stand - mask only. Back of the head lost.

AEABB170

EXTERNAL APPEARANCE

Cat shaped cylindrical bundle with false ears. Geometric patterning across the body area.

AEABB169

EXTERNAL APPEARANCE

Small cat mummy bundle with false head and ears. Bi-coloured linen wrappings.

AEABB168

EXTERNAL APPEARANCE

Very plain bundle with no decoration or facial detail. Wrappings cylindrical and monotone. In good condition with little to no damage.

AEABB167

EXTERNAL APPEARANCE

Large mishappen bundle. Wrappings have a similar pattern to EG614 - 'V' design.

AEABB166

EXTERNAL APPEARANCE

Very fragile and haphazardly wrapped. No decoration or discernible wrapping pattern.

AEABB165

EXTERNAL APPEARANCE

Conical shaped bundle with numerous layers of bandages, solid piece of background linen with applique ibis decoration. Bandaging is frayed and the contents feel loose and mobile. Hole visible, black layer underneath and bone…

AEABB164

EXTERNAL APPEARANCE

Conical shaped bundle layered with different linen layers and wrapped over with thread in a basket effect. Loose matter coming from a ?burn hole in RHS.

AEABB163

EXTERNAL APPEARANCE

Well wrapped bundle with herringbone decoration. Bi-colour bandaging with nemes headdress (no face but may have held a portrait originally). Collar consists of parallel strips of linen, four brown, six white, mirroring the design…

AEABB162

EXTERNAL APPEARANCE

Light grey coloured stone coffin with accompanying lid containing the remains of a ibis, the head of which is visible from the open aspect. Much amber coloured resin pieces and masses of bandages are visible surrounding the ibis…
